{
	"$schema": "https://aka.ms/codetour-schema",
	"title": "Navigation System & Dropdowns",
	"steps": [
		{
			"file": "src/data/navData.json",
			"description": "`navData.json` controls your site's navigation. Each entry has four possible fields:\n\n- **`key`** ‚Äî unique identifier (not displayed; used internally)\n- **`url`** ‚Äî the English path without locale prefix (e.g. `\"/about\"`); `<DynamicHeader />` applies `getLocalizedRoute()` automatically so French visitors get `/fr/a-propos`\n- **`label`** ‚Äî **an object with a key per locale**: `{ \"en\": \"About\", \"fr\": \"√Ä propos\" }` ‚Äî this is the text rendered in the nav bar\n- **`children`** ‚Äî optional array of sub-entries (same shape) for dropdown menus\n\nAdd, remove, or modify entries here to change your site's navigation structure.",
			"line": 2
		},
		{
			"file": "src/components/Header/DynamicHeader.astro",
			"description": "The `<DynamicHeader />` component imports navData.json and loops through each nav item. It checks if an item has children - if yes, it renders as a dropdown (li.cs-li.cs-dropdown). If no children, it renders as a regular link. The current page gets the **.cs-active** class automatically based on URL matching.",
			"line": 45
		},
		{
			"file": "src/components/Settings/Settings.astro",
			"description": "`Settings.astro` is the header's utility bar ‚Äî it renders the language switcher and dark mode toggle side by side. This is the file to edit when you want to swap or remove either component.\n\n**To swap the dark mode toggle**, replace the import and JSX tag. Two options live in `src/components/DarkMode/`:\n- `DarkModeToggle` ‚Äî simple moon/sun button\n- `ThemeSelect` ‚Äî three-way Light / Dark / Auto dropdown\n\n**To swap the language switcher**, replace the import and JSX tag. Two options live in `src/components/LanguageSwitch/`:\n- `TwoLocalesSelect` ‚Äî EN/FR button toggle\n- `MultiLocalesSelect` ‚Äî compact dropdown for 3+ locales\n\nThis component appears twice in `DynamicHeader` ‚Äî once inside the mobile slide-out panel (`cs-shown`) and once in the desktop nav bar (`cs-hidden`). Edits here apply to both breakpoints automatically.",
			"line": 1
		},
		{
			"file": "src/assets/js/nav.js",
			"description": "`nav.js` holds the script that adds interactivity to the navigation: **Mobile menu toggle** (hamburger button), **Dropdown accessibility** (keyboard navigation with Enter/Escape), and **Focus management**. It's wrapped in the `'astro:page-load'` event to work with Astro's View Transitions ‚Äî this ensures the script re-runs after each client-side navigation. Paste your CodeStitch JS here.",
			"line": 1
		}
	]
}
